==English==

===Etymology===
From the past participle stem of Latin [[perlustrare]], from [[per-]] + [[lustrare]] ‘wander through’, from [[lustrum]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/pəˈlʌstreɪt/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|perlustrat|ing}}

# to [[travel]] through an area in [[examination]] or [[survey]]

